Variation: the type series is fairly homogeneous, showing little variation in scale characteristics and number of femoral pores (
Table 1
). Like the holotype , all other specimens have five supraoculars, being the two first the smallest, six supralabials, four enlarged infralabials followed by two much smaller scales, six superciliars, and five preanal scales. All males have two femoral pores at each side; they are absent in females. Females are larger than males with a maximum snout-vent length of 34.4 and 29.0mm, respectively.
